summary: 3.- #KillingEve: La asesina encantadora y el regreso triunfante de Sandra Oh  Parecía imposible que se pudiera mejorar el...
caption:
3.- #KillingEve: La asesina encantadora y el regreso triunfante de Sandra Oh 

Parecía imposible que se pudiera mejorar el clásico juego del gato y el ratón presente en la mayoría de producciones de suspenso donde el bueno persigue al malo, pero después llegó “Killing Eve” y presentó no solo el regreso triunfante de Sandra Oh al mundo de las series, sino una nueva dinámica entre una sicaria y la mujer obsesionada con ella.

-> Lo mejor del 2018

summary: TV Shows of 2018 (in no particular order) ↳   Killing Eve Killing Eve was one of my most anticipated new shows of 2018. I had...
caption:
TV Shows of 2018 (in no particular order)

↳   Killing Eve

Killing Eve was one of my most anticipated new shows of 2018. I had fallen in love with Phoebe Waller-Bridge’s work on Fleabag and the idea of her creating a spy series was so intriguing. Killing Eve managed to meet and exceed my expectations, a masterful show that blends humour, spying, shocks and a game of cat vs cat incredibly well. Sandra Oh and Jodie Comer shine as the two leads and the chemistry between them is electric. I’m really excited for the second season and will follow Phoebe Waller-Bridge’s career whether she goes - really hope HBO pick up her latest pilot ‘Run’

summary: Having read the comments and having watched the episode, I have to admit that I need to watch the next episode of Killing Eve...
body:
Having read the comments and having watched the episode, I have to admit that I need to watch the next episode of Killing Eve before I make a judgment. Or maybe 1-2 more. The show didn’t grab me the way The Bridge or Preacher did where within minutes I knew I wanted more. 

So not giving up on it yet but not super enthusiastic either.
